{"questionId":"33005588","questionHtml":"<p>Use mathematical induction to prove that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>LHS</mtext><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>RHS</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>LHS</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>RHS</mtext></math> and so true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>R0</strong></em> for considering <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Subsequent marks after this <strong><em>R1</em></strong> are independent of this mark and can be awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>assume true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The assumption of truth must be apparent. Do not award <strong><em>M1</em></strong> for statements such as “let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>” or “assume that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> is true”. Subsequent marks after this <strong><em>M1</em></strong> are independent of this mark and can be awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempts to substitute for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>k</mi></msub></math> in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>since true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> if true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>, hence true for all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> To obtain the final <em><strong>R1</strong></em>, four of the previous six marks must have been awarded.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33005588","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.1g","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use mathematical induction to prove that un=u1rn-1-drn-1-1r-1, for n∈ℤ+.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"g","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}